# Blank Line Formatting

This project uses **Prettier** with `formatOnSave`. Never write code with a blank line between every statement.

## Rules

- **One statement per line** — not one blank line between every statement
- **Imports**: consecutive imports with no blank lines between them; one blank line after the import block
- **Functions**: one blank line between top-level functions; no blank lines between every line inside a function body
- **Blocks**: one blank line between logical sections (imports → state → functions → markup), not between each line
- **Before finishing**: scan edited files for double-spacing; remove stray blank lines so output matches existing project files

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — blank line after every line
import { foo } from './foo';

import { bar } from './bar';

let x = $state(0);

async function run() {

	event.preventDefault();

	const value = x.trim();

	if (!value) {

		return;

	}

}

// ✅ GOOD — normal spacing
import { foo } from './foo';
import { bar } from './bar';

let x = $state(0);

async function run() {
	event.preventDefault();
	const value = x.trim();
	if (!value) return;
}
```

When editing Svelte files, match the density of neighboring routes (e.g. `history/[id]/+page.svelte`): tight imports, logical section breaks only.
